<h2>Major Product Launch Platforms</h2>
<p>These are the highest-traffic platforms where products compete for daily attention. A strong launch here can drive thousands of visitors in a single day.</p>
<p><strong>1. <a href="https://www.producthunt.com">Product Hunt</a></strong>. The gold standard for product launches. Daily voting determines winners. A successful launch day can drive 1,000 to 10,000+ visits and a DR 90+ <a href="/glossary/backlinks/">backlink</a>. Prepare your launch with a hunter, tagline, and first comment.</p>
<p><strong>2. <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com">Hacker News (Show HN)</a></strong>. Y Combinator's community. Post your product with "Show HN:" prefix. Technical products thrive here. A front-page post delivers massive traffic within hours. No voting manipulation. Quality matters.</p>
<p><strong>3. <a href="https://betalist.com">BetaList</a></strong>. The go-to for pre-launch startups since 2010. Submit your landing page before launch to collect early signups. DR 75 dofollow backlink. Free submissions take 2-4 weeks. Paid gets faster approval.</p>
<p><strong>4. <a href="https://www.uneed.best">Uneed</a></strong>. Daily launch competitions with 8 to 15 products. Lower competition than Product Hunt. Winners earn a permanent listing and dofollow backlink. DR ~60. Paid option to skip the queue.</p>
<p><strong>5. <a href="https://devhunt.org">DevHunt</a></strong> ,  "Product Hunt for developer tools." GitHub-based authentication filters for real developers. DR 59 dofollow backlink. If you build for developers, this is a top pick.</p>
<p><strong>6. <a href="https://fazier.com">Fazier</a></strong>. Newer Product Hunt alternative with lower competition. Top 3 products each day earn a Product of the Day badge. Free to submit. Growing community of early adopters.</p>
<p><strong>7. <a href="https://microlaunch.net">MicroLaunch</a></strong>. Products stay listed for a full month instead of one day. Includes "Roasts" (feedback) and "Boosts" (upvotes). 50K monthly visitors. Better for products that need extended exposure.</p>
<p><strong>8. <a href="https://www.launchingnext.com">Launching Next</a></strong>. Over 44,000 startups featured. Daily and trending sections. Simple submission form. Good for early visibility without the pressure of a timed launch.</p>
<p><strong>9. <a href="https://peerlist.io">Peerlist</a></strong>. Part LinkedIn alternative, part launch platform. Weekly Spotlight limited to 50 products. 188K to 209K monthly visitors. Works best for B2B and developer products.</p>
<p><strong>10. <a href="https://dev.to">DEV Community</a></strong>. Developer community with 1M+ members. Publish a "Show DEV" post about your product. Free. Great for build-in-public narratives and technical product launches.</p>
<p><strong>11. <a href="https://appsumo.com">AppSumo</a></strong>. Marketplace for software deals. You set the price, earn 70-95% of revenue. Best for SaaS products offering lifetime deals. High-intent buyers already looking for new tools.</p>
<p><strong>12. <a href="https://openhunts.com">OpenHunts</a></strong>. Open-source alternative to Product Hunt. Hall of fame for top performers. Lower traffic but zero gatekeeping. Every submission gets listed.</p>
<p><strong>13. <a href="https://hypedesk.com">Hype Desk</a></strong>. Product launch platform featuring curated alternatives to Product Hunt. Free to submit. Growing directory focused on new and indie products.</p>
<p><strong>14. <a href="https://superlaunch.com">Super Launch</a></strong>. Startup launch directory with a small but active community. Free submission. Best for early-stage products looking for initial feedback and visibility.</p>
<p><strong>15. <a href="https://whatlaunched.com">WhatLaunched</a></strong>. Daily digest of new product launches. Focused on generating SEO backlinks for listed products. Free to submit. Good for long-tail organic discovery.</p>
