<h3>Optimize Every Listing</h3>
<p>Every directory gives you a chance to make a first impression. Do not waste it with a rushed listing.</p>
<ul>
<li>Write a unique description for each directory. Do not copy-paste the same text everywhere.</li>
<li>Use your primary keyword naturally in your product description.</li>
<li>Upload a high-quality logo and screenshot on every platform that allows images.</li>
<li>Link to a dedicated landing page, not just your homepage. Track traffic with UTM parameters.</li>
<li>Respond to every review, comment, and question on each platform.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Track What Works</h3>
<p>Set up UTM parameters for each directory submission:</p>
<p><code>https://yoursite.com?utm_source=producthunt&amp;utm_medium=directory&amp;utm_campaign=launch</code></p>
<p>After 30 days, check which directories drove:
- The most referral traffic
- The most signups or trials
- The highest-quality backlinks (check in <a href="/blog/google-search-console-guide/">Google Search Console</a>)</p>
<p>Double down on directories that convert. Update your listing monthly on high-performing platforms.</p>
<h3>Build a Submission Calendar</h3>
<p>Do not submit to all 209 directories in one day. Spread submissions across 4 to 6 weeks:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Week 1:</strong> 5 high-impact launches (Product Hunt, Hacker News, BetaList, G2, Capterra)</li>
<li><strong>Week 2:</strong> 15 software review sites and community platforms</li>
<li><strong>Week 3:</strong> 20 niche directories relevant to your product category</li>
<li><strong>Week 4:</strong> 20 more niche and regional directories</li>
<li><strong>Week 5-6:</strong> Remaining directories at 10 per day</li>
</ul>
<p>This pace avoids submission fatigue and lets you customize each listing.</p>
