<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How many startup directories should I submit to?</strong></p>
<p>Submit to every relevant directory where your target audience might discover your product. For most startups, that means 50 to 100 directories in the first month, then 10 to 20 per month ongoing. Quality of listing matters more than quantity. A well-optimized listing on Product Hunt outperforms 50 rushed submissions to low-traffic sites.</p>
<p><strong>Are startup directory submissions good for SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Directories with high <a href="/glossary/domain-authority/">domain authority</a> pass link equity to your site. Dofollow backlinks from Product Hunt (DR 90+), Crunchbase (DR 90+), and BetaList (DR 75) directly strengthen your backlink profile. Even nofollow links from reputable directories build brand signals that search engines recognize.</p>
<p><strong>What is the best alternative to Product Hunt?</strong></p>
<p>Uneed, DevHunt, and MicroLaunch are the three strongest Product Hunt alternatives in 2026. Uneed runs daily competitions with less competition. DevHunt focuses on developer tools with GitHub authentication. MicroLaunch gives products a full month of visibility instead of one day.</p>
<p><strong>Do paid directory submissions work?</strong></p>
<p>Paid submissions to legitimate review platforms like G2, Capterra, and Trustpilot are worth the investment because they drive high-intent buyer traffic. Paid submission services like SubmitSaaS save time but vary in quality. Avoid any service that promises "guaranteed backlinks" from low-quality directories.</p>
<p><strong>How long does it take to see results from directory submissions?</strong></p>
<p>Referral traffic starts within days of a Product Hunt launch. <a href="/blog/build-backlinks-for-blog/">SEO benefits from backlinks</a> typically appear in 60 to 90 days as search engines crawl and index your directory listings. Review site listings on G2 and Capterra drive steady traffic for months because buyers search these platforms continuously.</p>
<p><strong>Should I submit to directories before or after my product launch?</strong></p>
<p>Submit to pre-launch directories (BetaList, BetaPage, Betabound) 2 to 4 weeks before launch to collect early signups. Submit to launch platforms (Product Hunt, Hacker News) on launch day. Submit to review sites (G2, Capterra) and general directories in the weeks after launch when you have a polished product and real users.</p>
